soot

Class SootClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.tagkit.AbstractHost
      • soot.SootClass
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Host, Numberable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SootModuleInfo

    public class SootClass
extends AbstractHost
implements Numberable
    Soot representation of a Java class. They are usually created by a Scene, but can also be constructed manually through the given constructors.

      • checkLevel

        public void checkLevel(int level)
        Checks if the class has at least the resolving level specified. This check does nothing is the class resolution process is not completed.
        Parameters:
        level - the resolution level, one of DANGLING, HIERARCHY, SIGNATURES, and BODIES
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the resolution is at an insufficient level

      • checkLevelIgnoreResolving

        public void checkLevelIgnoreResolving(int level)
        Checks if the class has at least the resolving level specified. This check ignores the resolution completeness.
        Parameters:
        level - the resolution level, one of DANGLING, HIERARCHY, SIGNATURES, and BODIES
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the resolution is at an insufficient level
